'''''Bush Doctors''''' is a seven-part [[Australia]]n reality television series centred on the lives of a medical team at a rural hospital in [[Dubbo]], [[New South Wales]]. It debuted on the [[Seven Network]] on 3 February 2008 <ref>{{cite web | last= | first= |date=21 January 2008 | url= http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/story/0,26278,23081809-5013560,00.html | title=Jolene Anderson's greatest reality TV fear | work= | publisher=news.com.au | accessdate=}}</ref> and was narrated by ''[[All Saints (TV series)|All Saints]]'' star [[Jolene Anderson]].
This was her last show on channel 7 and she moved to Channel 10 to star in ''[[Rush (2008 TV series)|Rush]]''.
