'''Frances Ida''' "'''Kitty'''" '''Kain''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE}} (née '''Tyson''', 17 September 1908 &ndash; 16 August 1997) was a New Zealand dietitian and women’s air force leader. She was born in [[Dunedin]], New Zealand on 17 September 1908.<ref name="DNZB Kain">{{DNZB|last=Tunnicliff|first= Shirley|id=5k2|title=Frances Ida Kain|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> She was appointed an [[Order of the British Empire|Officer of the Order of the British Empire]] in the [[1949 New Year Honours (New Zealand)|1949 New Year Honours]].<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=38494 |date=31 December 1948 |page=34 |supp=y }}</ref>

