'''Storavatnet''' is a lake just southwest of the village of [[Loddefjord]] in [[Bergen]], [[Hordaland]] county, [[Norway]]. The {{convert|2.2|km|adj=on}} long lake is located in the borough of [[Laksevåg]], west of the city center of Bergen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bergenbyarkiv.no/bergenbyleksikon/arkiv/1407637|title=Storvatnet (Laksevåg)|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2014-09-13}}</ref>
There is a small man-made [[dam]] on the southwest coast, regulating the one natural outlet for the {{convert|1|km2|acre|adj=on}} lake. The major highway junction of [[Norwegian County Road 562]] and [[Norwegian National Road 555]] lies on the northern shore of the lake. Route 562 heads north to the [[Askøy Bridge]] going to the island of [[Askøy (island)|Askøy]]. Route 555 heads west to the [[Sotra Bridge]] which goes to the island of [[Sotra]]. The terminal in Loddefjord, near the lake is the proposed end of the new Loddefjord branch of the [[Bergen Light Rail]] system.
